<TITLE> 'ETPs or closure' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 19 (bdnews24.com)The government has ordered industries to install effluent treatment plants in six months, or else face closure. Industries minister Dilip Barua told reporters on Sunday after a discussion hosted by the Local Government Engineering Department in the capital that new industries must also get Effluent Treatment Plants. The High Court on June 23 ordered authorities to take steps to set upETPs in all the industries across the country by June next year. The court also ordered that all tanneries should be closed down by Feb 20 the same year. The orders came after Bangladesh Environment Lawyers' Association and Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh separately petitioned the court. bd
